   General Dynamics
   Wins Air Force Pact
   For $758.9 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
04/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4
</SO>
<CO>
   GD UTX MD CTC ROK T LIT
</CO>
<IN>
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<GV>
DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- General Dynamics Corp. won a $758.9 million
Air Force contract for F-16 aircraft and a $9.2 million Army
contract for Stinger missile services.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   United Technologies Corp. was given a $610.6 million Air
Force contract for jet fighter engines.
                                                                                                       

   McDonnell Douglas Corp. received a $90 million Navy
contract for F/A-18 aircraft.
                                                                                                       

   Contel Federal Systems Inc., a unit of Contel Corp., got a
$46.3 million Air Force contract for an automated weather
system.
                                                                                                       

   Rockwell International Corp. received a $42 million Air
Force contract for an information distribution system.
                                                                                                       

   American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. was issued a $32.1
million Navy contract for oceanographic equipment.
                                                                                                       

   Litton Systems, a unit of Litton Industries Inc., got a
$20.4 million Air Force pact for radar-warning receivers.
                                                                                                       

   CAE-Link Corp. got a $15.6 million Navy contract for
flight simulators.
