<HL>
   MCI Expands PrimeTime Plan
</HL>
<DATE>
04/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   MCIC T
</CO>
<IN>
TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- MCI Communications Corp. said it expanded
its PrimeTime calling plan to start at 5 p.m., rather than 7
p.m. weekdays.
   The change follows adjustments in American Telephone &amp;
Telegraph Co.'s Reach Out America plan that include a 15%
discount off standard evening rates between 5 p.m. and 10
p.m.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   MCI's PrimeTime plan, introduced last May, offers
customers an hour of out-of-state calling within the U.S. for
$8 a month, provided that the calls are made between 5 p.m.
and 8 a.m. weekdays, and on Saturdays and Sundays. Additional
calls during those hours are billed at the rate of $6.50 an
hour.
