<LP>
   MILAN -- Italy's consumer price index rose 0.4% in March
from February and was up 6.1% from a year earlier, Istat, the
state statistical institute, said.
   Istat said the index registered 104.4 in March, compared
with 104.0 in February and with 103.3 in January.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Calculation of the index has been revised as of January
1990 on the basis 1989 equals 100. Formerly the index was
calculated on a base of 1985 equals 100. The index isn't
seasonally adjusted.
   The March increase followed a 0.8% monthly rise in
February, when the year-to-year increase was 6.3%.
