<HL>
   World Business Index
   Grows at Sluggish Pace
</HL>
<DATE>
04/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST JAPAN EUROP CANDA
</CO>
<IN>
ECONOMIC NEWS (ECO)
INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIC NEWS AND STATISTICS (IEN)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- The world business cycle continues to grow at
a sluggish pace, the Conference Board reported.
   It said the composite leading index for 11 of the world's
major industrial countries grew at an annual rate of 2% in
December, the same as the prior month and six months earlier.
The leading indexes project future economic conditions.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Pacific region continues to show the greatest
strength, especially in Taiwan, where the leading index grew
at an 8% rate, the Conference Board said. Korea's leading
index followed closely behind at 7%. Japan's stood at 6%.
   Growth was sluggish in Europe. West Germany's grew at 5%,
and Italy at 1%. The leading indexes fell 1% in France and 2%
in the United Kingdom.
   Leading indexes both in the U.S. and Canada rose at a 1%
pace.
</TEXT>
