BANKS (BNK)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   SAN FRANCISCO -- Wells Fargo &amp; Co. said it completed two
purchases.
   The bank holding concern said it completed the purchase of
Torrey Pines Group, of Solana Beach, Calif., for about $74.5
million. The concern operates seven branches in San Diego
County. In addition, Wells Fargo completed the $160 million
purchase of Central Pacific Corp., a Bakersfield, Calif.,
concern with 28 branches.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The moves are part of Wells Fargo's strategy of aquiring
smaller banks with strong market shares in desirable consumer
markets.
