<IN>
FINANCIAL, ACCOUNTING, LEASING (FIN)
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   PHILLIPS PETROLEUM Co. (Bartlesville, Okla.) -- Moody's
Investors Service Inc. said it upgraded its ratings on this
energy concern's senior long-term debt to Baa-1 from Baa-2,
and subordinated debentures to Baa-2 from Baa-3. The rating
concern cited Phillips's accelerated debt-reduction program
and Moody's belief that the company should be able to fund
internally the bulk of its capital program at a level
sufficient to enhance its asset base.
   ---
</LP>
<TEXT>
   UNOCAL Corp. (Los Angeles) -- Moody's Investors Service
Inc. said it raised the long-term debt ratings on about $2.3
billion of Unocal's Union Oil Co. of California unit, citing
the company's progress in reducing debt and restructuring its
asset base to enhance profitability. The rating concern
raised the long-term debt rating on Union Oil's debentures,
notes, guaranteed Eurobonds and Euronotes and
pollution-control and industrial revenue bonds to Baa-1 from
Baa-2. The unit's shelf registration of senior debt
securities was also raised to Baa-1 from Baa-2. The Prime-2
ratings for commercial paper issued by Union Oil Co., Union
Oil Credit Corp. and Union Exploration Partners Limited
Partnership have been comfirmed, Moody's said. A spokesman
for Unocal, a diversified oil company, said it was "pleased
Moody's recognizes the progress the company is making."
</TEXT>
