<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)
</IN>
<LP>
   Maxtor Corp. said it made a $40 million offer to buy
substantially all of the assets of MiniScribe Corp., a
troubled Longmont, Colo., maker of computer disk drives.
   Maxtor, a maker of data-storage products, said the offer
consists of $20 million in cash, and $20 million in stock. In
